videos.headline: South Carolina's Wilson dominates in the paint
videos.description: A'ja Wilson backs her way into the paint and hits the turnaround jumper over multiple defenders for the Gamecocks.

article.description: Alexis Jennings had 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead No. 5 South Carolina to a 72-52 win over No. 14 Duke on Sunday.

article.headline: No. 5 S Carolina frontcourt shines, beats No. 14 Duke 72-52

images.name: Wilson, South Carolina win big over Duke
images.caption: A'ja Wilson scores 18 points en route to No. 5 South Carolina's 72-52 win over No. 14 Duke.

article.linkText: No. 5 S Carolina frontcourt shines, beats No. 14 Duke 72-52
article.story:
DURHAM, N.C. --  The women's basketball game scheduled for Sunday between No. 22 South Carolina and Duke is off due to wintry weather in the forecast.

The schools say they will try to reschedule the game this season.

The Blue Devils were set to host the Gamecocks in Cameron Indoor Stadium at 2 p.m. Sunday, but plans changed Saturday because of the possibility of several inches of snow coming to the region this weekend.
